e, brave’."]},{"name":"Brais","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Marcel, Aldea, Andre, Cecile, Fernande, Stephane.","French: altered form of   Bray  ."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William Bray was born in 1486, in Treswithian, Cornwall, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 3 sons with Margery. He died in 1518, at the age of 32."},"et":{"1486–1518":"1486–1518","1486–Female":"1486–Surnud","1500–Male":"1500–Surnud","1518–1570":"1518–1570","–1581":"–1581","1500":"1500","1486":"1486","1581":"1581","1570":"1570","1518":"1518","Treswithian, Cornwall, England, United Kingdom":"Treswithian, Cornwall, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Camborne, Cornwall, England":"Camborne, Cornwall, England"},"fi":{"1486–1518":"1486–1518","1486–Female":"1486–Kuollut","1500–Male":"1500–Kuollut","1518–1570":"1518–1570","–1581":"–1581","1500":"1500","1486":"1486","1581":"1581","1570":"1570","1518":"1518","Treswithian, Cornwall, England, United Kingdom":"Treswithian, Cornwall, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Camborne, Cornwall, England":"Camborne, Cornwall, England"},"fr":{"1486–1518":"1486–1518","1486–Female":"1486–Décédée","1500–Male":"1500–Décédé","1518–1570":"1518–1570","–1581":"–1581","1500":"1500","1486":"1486","1581":"15